[log] bash[80] stdout ## Detailed Implementation Nodes of Functions
[log] bash[80] stdout ### Node 1: Basic Paper Search
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function Description**: Implement the basic paper search function, supporting keyword queries and result quantity limits.
[log] bash[80] stdout **Core Algorithm**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - Build an arXiv search query
[log] bash[80] stdout - Apply field specifiers to optimize the search
[log] bash[80] stdout - Process search results and format the output
[log] bash[80] stdout **Input - Output Example**:
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout from arxiv_mcp_server.tools import handle_search
[log] bash[80] stdout import json
[log] bash[80] stdout # Basic search test
[log] bash[80] stdout async def test_basic_search():
[log] bash[80] stdout     result = await handle_search({
[log] bash[80] stdout         "query": "test query", 
[log] bash[80] stdout         "max_results": 1
[log] bash[80] stdout     })
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert len(result) == 1
[log] bash[80] stdout     content = json.loads(result[0].text)
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert content["total_results"] == 1
[log] bash[80] stdout     paper = content["papers"][0]
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert paper["id"] == "2103.12345"
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert paper["title"] == "Test Paper"
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert "resource_uri" in paper
[log] bash[80] stdout # Search response format
