[log] bash[80] stdout ### Node 5: Paper Download Lifecycle
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function Description**: Implement the complete paper download and conversion process, including status tracking and error handling.
[log] bash[80] stdout **Lifecycle Stages**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - Download the PDF file
[log] bash[80] stdout - Convert it to Markdown format
[log] bash[80] stdout - Track and update the status
[log] bash[80] stdout - Clean up temporary files
[log] bash[80] stdout **Input - Output Example**:
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout from arxiv_mcp_server.tools.download import handle_download, conversion_statuses
[log] bash[80] stdout # Complete download lifecycle test
[log] bash[80] stdout async def test_download_paper_lifecycle():
[log] bash[80] stdout     paper_id = "2103.12345"
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Initial download request
[log] bash[80] stdout     response = await handle_download({"paper_id": paper_id})
[log] bash[80] stdout     status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert status["status"] in ["converting", "success"]
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Check the final status
[log] bash[80] stdout     response = await handle_download({
[log] bash[80] stdout         "paper_id": paper_id, 
[log] bash[80] stdout         "check_status": True
[log] bash[80] stdout     })
[log] bash[80] stdout     final_status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert final_status["status"] in ["success", "converting"]
[log] bash[80] stdout # Download status response format
[log] bash[80] stdout {
[log] bash[80] stdout     "status": "converting",
[log] bash[80] stdout     "message": "Paper downloaded, conversion started",
[log] bash[80] stdout     "started_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00",
[log] bash[80] stdout     "resource_uri": "file:///path/to/paper.md"
[log] bash[80] stdout }
[log] bash[80] stdout # Conversion status tracking
[log] bash[80] stdout @dataclass
[log] bash[80] stdout class ConversionStatus:
[log] bash[80] stdout     paper_id: str
[log] bash[80] stdout     status: str  # 'downloading', 'converting', 'success', 'error'
[log] bash[80] stdout     started_at: datetime
[log] bash[80] stdout     completed_at: Optional[datetime] = None
[log] bash[80] stdout     error: Optional[str] = None
[log] bash[80] stdout ```
[log] bash[80] stdout ### Node 6: Existing Paper Handling
[log] bash[80] stdout **Function Description**: Handle repeated download requests for already downloaded papers to avoid redundant work.
[log] bash[80] stdout **Handling Strategy**:
[log] bash[80] stdout - Check local storage
[log] bash[80] stdout - Return the status of existing files
[log] bash[80] stdout - Provide the resource URI
[log] bash[80] stdout **Input - Output Example**:
[log] bash[80] stdout ```python
[log] bash[80] stdout # Existing paper test
[log] bash[80] stdout async def test_download_existing_paper():
[log] bash[80] stdout     paper_id = "2103.12345"
[log] bash[80] stdout     md_path = get_paper_path(paper_id, ".md")
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     # Create a test markdown file
[log] bash[80] stdout     md_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
[log] bash[80] stdout     with open(md_path, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
[log] bash[80] stdout         f.write("# Existing Paper\nTest content")
[log] bash[80] stdout     
[log] bash[80] stdout     response = await handle_download({"paper_id": paper_id})
[log] bash[80] stdout     status = json.loads(response[0].text)
[log] bash[80] stdout     assert status["status"] == "success"
[log] bash[80] stdout # Existing paper response
[log] bash[80] stdout {
[log] bash[80] stdout     "status": "success",
[log] bash[80] stdout     "message": "Paper already available",
[log] bash[80] stdout     "resource_uri": "file:///path/to/paper.md"
